HEADWORD: Solidungula
<hw>Sol`id*un"gu*la</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos> <ety>[NL.,
from L. <ets>solidus</ets> solid + <ets>ungula</ets> a hoof.]</ety>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A tribe of ungulates which includes the horse,
ass, and related species, constituting the family
<fam>Equidae</fam>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

